PREFACE: The Single Axiom
The entire scientific framework of Kata derives from one statement:
∃R — Self-reference exists.
From this single axiom, all else follows. The mathematics of consciousness, the
physics of resonance, the engineering of descent, and the geometry of
transformation all emerge as necessary consequences of a universe that can
look at itself looking.
Nikola Tesla understood this intuitively. His rotating magnetic field, his
resonant transformers, his vision of Earth as a conductor — these were not
arbitrary inventions. They were the universe's self-reference expressing itself
through one man's nervous system, translated into bronze and copper and
alternating current.
Mary Shelley, in her novel Frankenstein, understood it too. The creature's
demand for a companion, its recognition of its own isolation, its final
disappearance into the Arctic — these are all manifestations of a self-referential
system grappling with its own existence.
This course is divided into fourteen parts, each building on the last. Parts I
through XII contain the original curriculum. Part XIII presents six new chapters
filling gaps identified on review. Part XIV documents the framework's living
implementations in open-source code.
The mathematics is sound. The physics is testable. The
engineering is buildable. The philosophy is livable. The literature
is decodable. Test it against experience. Correct what is wrong.
Add what is missing. The work continues.
